datasets.name: 0bb7b433
queryLines:
with 
latest_retry_runs as (
    select * from [catalog].[schema].ops_run_details_vw where job_state__life_cycle_state not in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING")
    qualify row_number() over (partition by JOB_RUN_ID,task_original_attempt_run_id order by task_start_time desc) = 1
)
select 
job__tags__Team,
job__tags__Type,
coalesce(job__tags__Owner,run_as_user_name) as Users,
job__name as Jobs,
coalesce(task_error, case when task_state__state_message = '' then task_state__result_state else task_state__state_message end) task_error, 
case when trim(coalesce(job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end as Priority,
job_run_page_url, 
JOB_RUN_ID, 
job_start_time JobStartTime,
task_key, task_run_id, task_start_time, task_attempt_number, task_state__result_state, task_state__life_cycle_state, coalesce(job__tags__Domain,'Other') as Domain,
job__tags__Project as Project
from latest_retry_runs 
where task_state__result_state in ('FAILED','TIMEDOUT','CANCELED')
order by job_start_time desc

datasets.name: e9ace18d
205dbd0d
queryLines:
with 
latest_retry_runs as (
    select * from [catalog].[schema].ops_run_details_vw where job_state__life_cycle_state not in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING")
    qualify row_number() over (partition by JOB_RUN_ID,task_original_attempt_run_id order by task_start_time desc) = 1
),
failed_run_ids as (
    select distinct JOB_RUN_ID from latest_retry_runs
    where task_state__result_state in ('FAILED','TIMEDOUT','CANCELED') 
)
select 
    coalesce(job__tags__Owner,jd.run_as_user_name) Users,
    jd.job__name as Jobs,
    coalesce(jd.job__tags__Domain,'Other') as Domain, 
    case when trim(coalesce(job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end as Priority,
    r.JOB_RUN_ID as JobRuns, 
    timestamp_millis(r.job_start_time) as JobStartTime, 
    case when r.job_state__life_cycle_state in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING") then 1 else 0 end as running,
    case when fr.JOB_RUN_ID is not null then 1 else 0 end as failed,
    case when fr.JOB_RUN_ID is null and r.job_state__result_state = 'SUCCESS' then 1 else 0 end as success,
    case when fr.JOB_RUN_ID is null and r.job_state__life_cycle_state in ('SKIPPED') then 1 else 0 end as skipped,
    case when coalesce(job_run_duration,0) = 0 then (job_setup_duration + job_execution_duration + job_cleanup_duration) else job_run_duration end as run_duration,
    jd.job__tags__Project as Project,
    jd.job__tags__Team ,
    jd.job__tags__Type
from 
[catalog].[schema].job_run_details r
left join [catalog].[schema].job_details jd on r.job_id = jd.job_id 
left join failed_run_ids fr on fr.JOB_RUN_ID = r.JOB_RUN_ID 
-- where coalesce(job__tags__Owner,jd.run_as_user_name) is not null
order by failed desc

datasets.name: f845b9f3
queryLines:
with errors as (
  select 
    job_run_name,coalesce(job__tags__Owner,run_as_user_name) as run_as_user_name,task_error,
    ai_query("databricks-meta-llama-3-3-70b-instruct","generate the summary of the error in 20-30 words and the reolution in another 20-30 words- "|| task_error ||"Output Format should be exactly like below - 
    Error Summary: 
    Error Resolution: ")  as ai_error_summary_and_res,
    max(job_start_time) as Error_last_occured_on, 
    min(job_start_time) first_occurance_last10Days,
    max(job_link) as job_link, 
    min(case when trim(coalesce(job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end) as Priority,
    max(job__tags__Domain) as Domain,
    count(*) failure_count,
    job__tags__Team,
    job__tags__Type,
    job__tags__Project as Project
  from 
    [catalog].[schema].ops_run_details_vw where task_state__result_state = 'FAILED' and to_date(job_start_time) >= date_add(current_date(), -100 ) 
  group by 
    job_run_name,coalesce(job__tags__Owner,run_as_user_name),task_error,job__tags__Team,
    job__tags__Type,Project
)
select * from errors 
where Error_last_occured_on >= date_add(current_date(), -:x_days )
order by failure_count desc, job_run_name

datasets.name: 6c6ceae4
queryLines:
select job__name,
    case
        when (job__git_source__git_provider is null) then false
        else true
    end as Check_RunningFromGIT,
    case
        when (
            not array_contains(
                coalesce(job__email_notifications__on_failure,array('')),
                '[failure_email_alert@email.com]'
            )
        ) then false
        else true
    end as Check_FailureEmailAlert,
    timestamp_millis(created_time) created_time,
    creator_user_name,
    run_as_user_name as run_as_user_name,
    job__tags__Owner as owner_tag,
    job__tags__Domain as Domain,
    case when trim(coalesce(job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end as Priority,
    Job_link,
    job__email_notifications__on_failure,
    job__tags__Project as Project,
    job__tags__Team,
    job__tags__Type
from [catalog].[schema].job_details
where is_job_deleted = 'no' 
and 
(
        job__git_source__git_provider is null
        or not array_contains(
            coalesce(job__email_notifications__on_failure,array('')),
            '[failure_email_alert@email.com]'
        )
    )

datasets.name: 7351008c
queryLines:
with res_set as (
  select job_run_name, job_id, job_run_id, job_start_time, job_state__life_cycle_state as job_life_cycle_state, job_run_page_url  
  from [catalog].[schema].job_run_details where job_state__life_cycle_state in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING") --and job_id != 209055840362430
),
avg_run as (
  select 
    job_id,
    floor(avg(case when coalesce(job_run_duration,0) = 0 then (job_setup_duration + job_execution_duration + job_cleanup_duration) else job_run_duration end)) as avg_elapsed_time_last30Days
  from [catalog].[schema].job_run_details where date(timestamp_millis(job_start_time)) between date_add(current_date(),-30) and current_date() and 
  job_id in (select job_id from res_set) and 
  job_state__result_state = 'SUCCESS'
  group by job_id
),
last_updated_job_run_details as (
  select max(timestamp) as last_status_updated_ts from (describe history [catalog].[schema].job_run_details) where operation = 'MERGE'
)
select 
  job_run_page_url,job_run_name,timestamp_millis(job_start_time) job_start_time, 
  ceil((unix_millis(last_status_updated_ts) - job_start_time)/60000) || ' minutes' job_elapsed_time ,
  ceil(avg_elapsed_time_last30Days/60000)|| ' minutes' avg_elapsed_time_last30Days_sec, 
  round((unix_millis(last_status_updated_ts) - job_start_time)/avg_elapsed_time_last30Days,2) elapsed_x_times_avg, 
  case 
    when ((unix_millis(last_status_updated_ts) - job_start_time)/avg_elapsed_time_last30Days) >= 2 then True else False 
  end as long_running_review_X_avg, 
  case when trim(coalesce(jd.job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end as Priority,
  jd.job__tags__Project as Project,
  jd.job__tags__Team,
  jd.job__tags__Type
from res_set rs
join avg_run av using (job_id)
join [catalog].[schema].job_details jd on rs.job_id = jd.job_id
join last_updated_job_run_details last_exec on 1 = 1
order by long_running_review_X_avg desc

datasets.name: b2f34f79
queryLines:
WITH latest_failed_runs AS (
    SELECT 
        task_job_run_id, 
        COALESCE(task_error, CASE WHEN task_state__state_message = '' THEN task_state__result_state ELSE task_state__state_message END) AS task_error 
    FROM [catalog].[schema].ops_run_details_vw 
    WHERE job_state__result_state IN ('FAILED','TIMEDOUT','CANCELED') 
        AND task_state__state_message != 'An upstream task failed.'
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY JOB_ID ORDER BY task_start_time DESC) = 1
),
last_jobrun AS (
    SELECT 
        COALESCE(job__tags__Owner, jd.run_as_user_name) AS Users,
        jd.job__name AS Jobs,
        COALESCE(jd.job__tags__Domain, 'Other') AS Domain, 
        CASE 
            WHEN TRIM(COALESCE(job__tags__Priority, '')) = '' THEN 'P4' 
            ELSE TRIM(UPPER(SPLIT(job__tags__Priority, '-')[0])) 
        END AS Priority,
        r.JOB_RUN_ID AS JobRuns, 
        TIMESTAMP_MILLIS(
            CASE
                WHEN job_start_time = 0 THEN NULL
                ELSE job_start_time
            END
        ) AS jobStartTime,
        TIMESTAMP_MILLIS(
            CASE
                WHEN job_end_time = 0 THEN NULL
                ELSE job_end_time
            END
        ) AS jobEndTime,
        case 
            when r.job_state__life_cycle_state in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING") then 'RUNNING'
            when r.job_state__result_state = 'SUCCESS' then 'SUCCESS'
            -- when r.job_state__life_cycle_state in ('SKIPPED') then 'SKIPPED'
            when r.job_state__result_state in ('FAILED','TIMEDOUT','CANCELED') then 'FAILED'
            end as job_status,
        jd.job__tags__Project AS Project,
        r.job_run_page_url,
        jd.job__tags__Team,
        jd.job__tags__Type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY r.job_id ORDER BY job_start_time DESC) AS run_rn
    FROM 
        [catalog].[schema].job_run_details r
        INNER JOIN [catalog].[schema].job_details jd ON r.job_id = jd.job_id
    WHERE is_job_deleted = 'no' 
        AND r.job_state__life_cycle_state NOT IN ('SKIPPED') 
    QUALIFY run_rn = 1
)
SELECT 
    lt.*,
    COALESCE(lf.task_error, 'NA') AS task_error
FROM last_jobrun lt
LEFT JOIN latest_failed_runs lf ON lf.task_job_run_id = lt.JobRuns AND lt.job_status = 'FAILED' 
ORDER BY jobStartTime DESC

datasets.name: a3a149c2
queryLines:
with 
latest_retry_runs as (
    select * from [catalog].[schema].ops_run_details_vw where job_state__life_cycle_state not in ("PENDING","RUNNING","TERMINATING")
    qualify row_number() over (partition by JOB_RUN_ID,task_original_attempt_run_id order by task_start_time desc) = 1
),
failures as (
select 
job__tags__Team,
job__tags__Type,
coalesce(job__tags__Owner,run_as_user_name) as Users,
job__name as Jobs,
coalesce(task_error, case when task_state__state_message = '' then task_state__result_state else task_state__state_message end) task_error, 
case when trim(coalesce(job__tags__Priority,'')) = '' then "P4" else trim(upper(split(job__tags__Priority,'-')[0])) end as Priority,
job_run_page_url, 
JOB_RUN_ID, 
job_start_time JobStartTime,
task_key, task_run_id, task_start_time, task_attempt_number, task_state__result_state, task_state__life_cycle_state, coalesce(job__tags__Domain,'Other') as Domain,
job__tags__Project as Project,
Job_link
from latest_retry_runs 
where task_state__result_state in ('FAILED','TIMEDOUT','CANCELED')
),
stats as (
select 
job__tags__Team,
job__tags__Type,
Jobs, Job_link,
first_value(Priority) over (partition by Jobs order by JobStartTime desc ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING) as priority, 
first_value(domain) over (partition by Jobs order by JobStartTime desc ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING) as domain, --count(failed_date) as Failed_days, sum(Total_Failure_Count) as Total_Failure_Count, 
first_value(Users) over (partition by Jobs order by JobStartTime desc ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING) as Users,


to_date(JobStartTime) failed_date 
-- count(*) as `Total_Failure_Count`
-- count(distinct to_date(JobStartTime)) as `Failed_Days`
--count(*) over(partition by Jobs, Priority, domain) as `Total Failure Count (30 days)`, 
--count(distinct to_date(JobStartTime)) over(partition by Jobs, Priority, domain) as `Failed Days (30 days)`
from failures 
where 
to_date(JobStartTime) >= date_add(current_date(), -:x_days )
-- group by all
),
stats_x as (
select 
job__tags__Team,
job__tags__Type,
Jobs, Job_link, 
priority, 
domain, --count(failed_date) as Failed_days, sum(Total_Failure_Count) as Total_Failure_Count, 
Users,
failed_date,
count(*) as `Total_Failure_Count`
-- sum(Total_Failure_Count) over(partition by Jobs, Priority, domain) as `Total_Failure_Count_30_days`,
-- count(failed_date) over(partition by Jobs, Priority, domain) as `Failed_Days_30_days`
from stats
group by all
)
select 
job__tags__Team,
job__tags__Type,
Jobs, Job_link, Priority, domain, users, count(failed_date) as failed_days, sum(Total_Failure_Count) as Total_Failure_Count --, Failed_Days_30_days, Total_Failure_Count_30_days
 from stats_x
-- where failed_date between :start_date and :end_date
group by all

datasets.name: 0085e608
queryLines:
select jd.job_id, max(jd.Job_link) as job_link, max(jd.job__name) job_name, us.sku_name, sum(usage_quantity) as dbus from system.billing.usage us
inner join [catalog].[schema].job_details jd on jd.job_id = us.usage_metadata.job_id
where us.usage_date >= :usage_date_range.min and us.usage_date <= :usage_date_range.max
group by jd.job_id, us.sku_name
order by dbus desc,jd.job_id, us.sku_name 
limit :top_x_consumption

queryLines:
with runs as (select job_id, max(period_end_time) run_end_time
from system.lakeflow.job_run_timeline
group by job_id
)
select 
 jd.job_id
,timestamp_millis(created_time) created_time
,creator_user_name
,run_as_user_name
,job__email_notifications__on_failure
,job__name
,job__schedule__pause_status
,job__schedule__quartz_cron_expression
,job__schedule__timezone_id
,job__timeout_seconds
,job__git_source__git_branch
,job__git_source__git_provider
,job__git_source__git_url
,job__job_clusters
,Job_link
,is_job_deleted
,to_date(runs.run_end_time) as last_run_time
,coalesce(job__tags__Team,'NA') as job__tags__Team
,job__tags__Type
,job__tags__Owner
,job__tags__Project
,job__tags__Domain as Domain
,job__tags__Priority as Priority
from [catalog].[schema].job_details jd
inner join runs on runs.job_id = jd.job_id
where is_job_deleted is False
order by last_run_time desc;

with runs as (select job_id, max(period_end_time) run_end_time
from system.lakeflow.job_run_timeline
group by job_id
)
select 
 jd.job_id
,jd.job__name
,timestamp_millis(created_time) created_time
,creator_user_name
,Job_link
,is_job_deleted
,to_date(runs.run_end_time) as last_run_time
,coalesce(job__tags__Team,'NA') as job__tags__Team
,job__tags__Type
,job__tags__Owner
,job__tags__Project
,job__tags__Domain as Domain
,job__tags__Priority as Priority
from [catalog].[schema].job_details jd
inner join runs on runs.job_id = jd.job_id
where is_job_deleted is False and
coalesce(to_date(runs.run_end_time),'1999-01-01') < date_add(current_date(), -:last_run_days)
order by last_run_time desc;
